Node.Notes: Apparently indicates that the fact about to be stated is a consequence of the fact which has just been stated. Perhaps related to other possible unusual usage in rom6:11.
Some take as middle. More likely passive.
Assumes list with three adverbial participial clauses (second and third one elided participle being).

Node.RefEnglish: {unrighteousness, wickedness, greediness, evil, of envy, murder, strife, deceit, malice, whisperers, backbiters, God-haters, insolent, arrogant, boasters, inventors disobedient, senseless, faithless, unaffectionate, merciless;}
